casebody.data:
Thursday, March 3, 1994

MISCELLANEOUS DISMISSALS

94-471. State ex rel. Caviness v. Cleveland City Council.

In Mandamus. This cause originated in this court on the filing of a complaint for a writ of mandamus regarding an expedited election matter. Upon consideration of relator’s motion to withdraw verified complaint for peremptory writ of mandamus and application for alternative writ of mandamus,

IT IS ORDERED by the court that the motion to withdraw be, and the same is hereby, granted.

IT IS FURTHER ORDERED by the court that this cause be, and the same is hereby, dismissed.
